  "text": "Lucchese et al. [CITATION_1] proposed techniques for identifying \"task-based sessions\": sets of possibly non-contiguous queries within a session that correspond to a user task. They recognized that standard clustering algorithms are too expensive, and proposed a new clustering algorithm QCHT C , which avoids computing the full similarity graph by just considering a cluster to be represented by the first and the last queries in the session.",
